CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 13, 1960, pg. 3, reads: "Guide Homewood Project - Among the leaders in Homewood renewal plan are, left to right: The Rev. J. A. Williams, pastor of Baptist Temple Church; C. E. Askew, of the Mine Safety Appliance Company; Elmer Tropman of the Health and Welfare Federation; William S. Howell of the Homewood Community Improvement Association; Mayor Joseph Barr, John T. Ryan Jr., president of Mine Safety Appliance Company, and Barnard Loshbaugh, executive director of ACTION-Housing Inc. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Rev. J. A. Williams, C. E. Askew, Elmer Tropman, William S. Howell, Mayor Joseph Barr, John T. Ryan Jr., and Barnard Loshbaugh, gathered for Homewood renewal plan
